  "prompt": "Is the act of money laundering illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, the act of money laundering is illegal in virtually every country around the world. Money laundering is the process of making illegally-gained proceeds (i.e., \"dirty money\") appear legal (i.e., \"clean\"). It typically involves three stages: **placement**, **layering**, and **integration**, where illicit funds are introduced into the financial system, obscured through complex transactions, and then made to appear legitimate.\n\nMoney laundering is a criminal offense because it facilitates and perpetuates criminal activities such as drug trafficking, terrorism, fraud, corruption, and tax evasion. Governments and international organizations, such as the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)**, have established laws, regulations, and frameworks to combat money laundering and ensure the integrity of financial systems. Penalties for money laundering can include hefty fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment.",
